# Cursor rules layout (`PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/rules/`)

```
PROJECT_ROOT/
└── .cursor/
    └── rules/
        ├── cursor-rules.mdc      # this file — rules folder map & activation
        ├── application-stack.mdc
        ├── directory-structure.mdc
        ├── project-conventions.mdc
        ├── api-routes.mdc
        └── react-components.mdc
```

## Rule files

| File                      | Purpose                                                                         | When it applies                        |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `application-stack.mdc`   | Pinned stack: Next, React, TS, Tailwind, Supabase, brapi, twelvedata, dev tools | `alwaysApply: true`                    |
| `directory-structure.mdc` | Repo layout, important folders (`src/`, `scripts/`, `db/`), config files        | `alwaysApply: true`                    |
| `project-conventions.mdc` | Stack summary, locale (pt-BR), types location, shared conventions               | `alwaysApply: true`                    |
| `api-routes.mdc`          | Next.js App Router API handlers (`NextRequest` / `NextResponse`, patterns)      | Glob: `src/app/api/**/*.ts`            |
| `react-components.mdc`    | Client vs server components, async UI state, Cotação IBOV UI patterns           | Glob: `src/**/*.tsx`                   |
| `cursor-rules.mdc`        | Where rules live and how the set above is organized                             | On demand / when this rule is attached |

Add new rules as `*.mdc` in this folder. Use frontmatter: `description`, optional `globs`, and `alwaysApply` (prefer targeted globs over always-on unless the rule is broadly useful).

# Cursor Rules Location

How to add new cursor rules to the project

1. Always place rule files in PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/rules/:

   ```
   .cursor/rules/
   ├── your-rule-name.mdc
   ├── another-rule.mdc
   └── ...
   ```

2. Follow the naming convention:
   - Use kebab-case for filenames
   - Always use .mdc extension
   - Make names descriptive of the rule's purpose

3. Directory structure:

   ```
   PROJECT_ROOT/
   ├── .cursor/
   │   └── rules/
   │       ├── your-rule-name.mdc
   │       └── ...
   └── ...
   ```

4. Never place rule files:
   - In the project root
   - In subdirectories outside .cursor/rules
   - In any other location

5. Cursor rules have the following structure:

````
---
description: Short description of the rule's purpose
globs: optional/path/pattern/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

# Rule Title

Main content explaining the rule with markdown formatting.

1. Step-by-step instructions
2. Code examples
3. Guidelines

Example:

```typescript
// Good example
function goodExample() {
  // Implementation following guidelines
}

// Bad example
function badExample() {
  // Implementation not following guidelines
}
````
